Slovenia Sostanj Plant Gets First EIB Loan Tranche, Finance Says

-- B y   B o r i s   C e r n i
-- 
2011-02-17T17:02:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-17/slovenia-sostanj-plant-gets-first-eib-loan-tranche-finance-says.html
Termoelektrarna Sostanj d.o.o.
received the first tranche of a total 550 million-euro ($750
million) loan from the  European Investment Bank  to upgrade
Slovenia’s state-owned thermal power plant, Finance newspaper
 reported , citing the company.  The 110 million-euro tranche was released after the power
plant, based in Sostanj in northern Slovenia, secured an
environmental permit, an agreement from the government and
ensured the rest of the financing, the Ljubljana-based business
daily said.  The total value of the Sostanj plant upgrade is estimated
at about 1.2 billion euros and is Slovenia’s biggest energy
investment since the country gained independence two decades
ago.  Alstom SA  of France will provide the equipment.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Boris Cerni in Ljubljana at 
 bcerni@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
